			"Payroll and Administration Officer<p></p><p></p><p>Company:</p>Boeing Aerostructures Australia Pty Ltd<p></p><p></p><p>Job ID:</p>00000427131<p></p><p></p><p>Date Posted:</p>2024-05-22<p></p><p></p><p>Location:</p>AUS - Port Melbourne, Australia<p></p><p></p><p>Job Description Qualifications:</p><p>At Boeing, we are all innovators on a mission to connect, protect, explore and inspire. From the sea bed to outer space, you’ll learn and grow, contributing to work that shapes the world. Find your future with us.<br/><br/>We are currently seeking an early career Payroll and Administration Officer to join our team on a 12 month maximum-term contract based at our Port Melbourne facility. This is an excellent development opportunity for someone that has an interest in learning and developing their career in the Payroll function.<br/><br/>Position Responsibilities:</p><p>Reporting into the Finance Manager, as the Payroll and Administration Officer, you will be trained in the following statement of work:</p><ul><li>End to end full function Payroll for approximately 900 weekly (Award) and monthly (Non-Award) paid employees utilizing PeopleSoft 9.2</li><li>Carry out day to day payroll functions of data processing, including overtime calculations, ad hoc manual payments and manager/employee queries</li><li>Maintenance of employee details in PeopleSoft 9.2 Time and Labour and Global Payroll modules</li><li>Effective customer service to employee pay queries and timely resolutions on a day to day basis</li><li>Follow process, procedures and policies as set by Boeing Aerostructures Australia</li><li>Effective business partnering with HR, Operations, IT and Finance where required</li><li>Expat payroll</li><li>General administration duties as required<br/></li></ul><p>Basic Qualifications (Required Skills / Experience):</p><ul><li>A keen interest in developing a career in Payroll. Some prior experience in Payroll is advantageous although not essential</li><li>Exceptional planning, time management and organizational skills</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li><li>A high level of attention to detail and comfortable working in a fast paced, autonomous and process driven environment</li><li>Good teaming and interpersonal skills with the ability to engage across a diverse workforce</li><li>Proactive and results oriented approach</li><li>Full, unrestricted Australian working rights<br/></li></ul><p>Preferred Qualifications:</p><ul><li>Qualification in Business, Commerce, Finance or a related discipline preferred but not essential</li></ul><p></p><p>Additional information:</p><p>This is a Non EBA IJC 9AHYIB position. The successful candidate will be required to complete pre-employment checks and a 6 month probationary period.<br/><br/>Applications for this position will be accepted until Sunday 9th June 2024.<br/><br/>How to Apply:<br/>To apply, please upload your resume and a cover letter answering the following application questions:</p><ul><li>What attracts you to develop a career in Payroll with Boeing Aerostructures Australia?</li><li>What skills and experience will you bring?</li><li>What do you hope to experience during your maximum-term contract?</li></ul><p><br/>About our benefits:</p><ul><li>On the job training and development with experienced BAA employees</li><li>Work for an industry leader in Aerospace</li><li>Competitive remuneration</li><li>Additional annual ‘Boeing Day off’</li><li>Strong career opportunities</li><li>Access to Boeing Discount Program – an exclusive retail and services discount marketplace including discounts for health insurance, travel and accommodation</li><li>Salary packaging options available</li><li>Health and wellbeing benefits including annual flu vaccinations and Employee Assistance Program</li><li>Join community and social groups</li></ul><p><br/>About us:<br/><br/>Boeing Aerostructures Australia is Australia's leading designer and manufacturer of composite flight control components for commercial aircraft. We are renowned for our collaborative and supportive working environment and for the high caliber of our people. We are passionate about improving peoples' lives through increasing global mobility with our iconic planes including the production of the 737, 777 and 787 models.<br/><br/>At Boeing Aerostructures Australia, we are committed to creating an inclusive and incident and injury free workplace, where employees can realise their career goals and make a positive contribution to Boeing’s success.<br/><br/>If this role is you and you're excited by the opportunity to be part of building something amazing, we welcome your application.</p><p></p><p></p><p>Boeing is the world's largest aerospace company and leading manufacturer of commercial airplanes and defense, space and security systems. We are engineers and technicians. Skilled scientists and thinkers. Bold innovators and dreamers. Join us, and you can build something better for yourself, for our customers and for the world.</p><p></p><p></p><p>Relocation:</p>No relocation available<p></p><p></p><p>Export Control Requirement:</p><p></p><p></p><p>Safety Sensitive:</p>This is not a safety sensitive position<p></p><p></p><p>Contingent Upon Award Program</p>This position is not contingent upon program award<p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p>Experience Level:</p>Individual Contributor - B<p></p><p></p><p>Job Type:</p>Max Term (Fixed Term)<p></p><p></p><p>Job Code:</p>9AHYIB (909)<p></p><p></p><p>Our Boeing Australia employers are committed to inclusive and flexible workplaces and encourage people of all backgrounds, ages, genders, disabilities and for veterans and Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples to apply.</p>",
